Quote:  The supple-jack is to be met with in all parts of the woods; and there is here also a species of the myrtle similar to that found in various parts of New South Wales. Another part of it grows in the country about Dusky Bay, an infusion of which was drank [sic] by the crew of the Endeavour, as a substitute for tea.
